Package cx.corp.lacuna.core

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    MemoryReader
    Provides methods for reading bytes from the memory of a native process and constructing common Java types from them.
    MemoryWriter
    Provides methods for writing bytes and common Java data types to the memory of a native process.
    NativeProcessCollector
    Provides functionality for collecting the details of a native process into a NativeProcess model object using the provided process identifier.
    NativeProcessEnumerator
    Provides functionality for fetching a list of all running processes on the host computer.
    PidEnumerator
    Provides functionality for fetching a list of all of the running processes' identifiers.
    RawMemoryReader
    Provides functionality for reading a region of bytes from a native process's memory.
    RawMemoryWriter
    Provides functionality for writing an array of bytes to a native process's memory.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    LacunaBootstrap
    Provides easy access to the main Lacuna classes, bootstrapped to the correct platform.
    MemoryReaderImpl
    MemoryWriterImpl
    NativeProcessEnumeratorImpl
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    TypeSize  
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    MemoryAccessException
    Thrown to indicate that reading or writing to a native process's memory failed.
    ProcessEnumerationException
    Thrown to indicate that an error occurred while enumerating the running processes.
    ProcessOpenException
    Thrown to indicate that opening a handle to a native process failed.
